# Regression guardrails

## After edits here

- Run `npm run full-check` before considering the task done (see agent full-check rule).
- For **flow or board behavior** changes, also run `npm run test:integration` once as a fast focused loop (optional but encouraged before relying only on the full suite).

## Regression fix discipline

When reproducing a bug: add a **failing test or scenario step** (or assertion) first when practical, then fix—see [`testing-commands.mdc`](testing-commands.mdc) and [`docs/adr/0002-integration-scenario-regression-locks.md`](../../docs/adr/0002-integration-scenario-regression-locks.md).

## Large orchestrator refactors

Run a **readonly second pass** (human or sub-agent): violates [state axioms](state-axioms.mdc)? Missing tests? Scenario coverage for changed flows?

## Durable decisions

Cross-cutting “why” that should survive refactors: add a short ADR under [`docs/adr/`](../../docs/adr/README.md); keep [architecture-decisions.mdc](architecture-decisions.mdc) for agent context without duplicating long prose.
